Let $f(x)$ be a continuous function on $[0,1]$ such that $f(0) = 0$ and $f(1) = 1$. The athlete's skills can be represented as the function $f(x)$, while the coach's approval rating can be represented as the function $g(x)$, where $g(x) = 1 - f(x)$.

If the coach only approves of the athlete's skills when the athlete behaves non-rebelliously, then
\begin{align*}
\int_{0}^{1} g(x)\, dx = \int_{0}^{1}(1 - f(x))\, dx = 1 - \int_{0}^{1} f(x)\, dx.
\end{align*}

Suppose the athlete's skills increase linearly, such that $f(x) = x$ for all $x \in [0,1]$. Find the function $g(x)$ and compute the coach's overall approval rating.
